# Appendix E — Where slats live in Lacuna

Every system that speaks slat. Framing choice, purpose, one example
per system.

## The tree at a glance

```
docs/atoms/                          .slat  hand-authored, whole-document
  incident-narratives/*.slat         .slat  Weave-2 teaching material
  card-insides/chat/*.slat           .slat  chat artifact content
  card-insides/error/*.slat          .slat  error card content
  card-insides/book-page/*.slat      .slat  book-page card content
  card-insides/abduction/*.slat      .slat  reasoning-trace atoms
  correction-pairs/*.slat            .slat  before/after training pairs

~/.lacuna/mailboxes/*.slatl          .slatl streamed messages
~/.lacuna/logs/*.slatl               .slatl Loam ingest streams
~/.cortex/motoi/*.slat              .slat  cortex slices
~/.cortex/motoi/mood.slatl          .slatl mood-change events

carts/community/*.slat               .slat  published community carts
carts/local/*.slat                   .slat  personal carts (unsigned)
carts/saves/*.slat                   .slat  cart save states (signed)

tests/vectors.slat                   .slat  reader/writer fixture
```

## Curator

Curator's L1/L2 tools produce and consume slats. Each verb signature
is documented in the reference manual. Mailboxes at
`~/.lacuna/mailboxes/curator-*.slatl`.

Example — an atom-authoring event:

```
(event :ts #inst \"2026-07-11T18:22:00Z\" :kind \"atom.authored\"
       :atom-id \"atm-scheme-lambda-001\" :by 'zain)
```

## Forge

Forge's training pipeline reads corpus `.slatl` files, writes
checkpoint `.slat` files, streams `event` records into Loam.

Example — a training-iter event:

```
(event :ts #inst \"2026-07-11T18:22:00Z\" :kind \"training.iter\"
       :iter 350 :train-loss 4.876 :val-loss 3.745)
```

## Cortex

Cortex is the memory substrate. Every slice is a slat. See Chapter
14. Files live at `~/.cortex/motoi/<key>.slat` or under
`~/.cortex/motoi/streams/<key>.slatl` for streams.

Example — a mood snapshot:

```
(snapshot :ts #inst \"2026-07-11T18:22:00Z\"
          :subject 'motoi.mood
          :body (mood :valence 0.6 :arousal 0.4))
```

## Foreman / worker mailboxes

The foreman writes `.slatl` mailboxes for workers. Workers tail
theirs and dispatch. See Chapter 13.

Example — a training-start message:

```
(message :v 1 :from 'foreman :to 'worker/mlx-1
         :ts #inst \"2026-07-11T18:22:00Z\"
         :detail (start-training-run :seed 4137 :max-iter 68520))
```

## Artifact bus

Artifacts serialize as `artifact-state`. Chat, IDE, RAG, animation,
game — same shape. See Chapter 5.

Example — a chat state:

```
(artifact-state :type 'chat
                :id \"chat-2026-07-11-alfred\"
                :state ((messages ((user \"hi\") (runtime "hi\")))))
```

## Book of Reason / incident narratives

Every teachable event the runtime sees produces an `incident-narrative`
under `docs/atoms/incident-narratives/`. See Chapter 5, entry 15.

## Book of Automations / carts

Every cart is a `cart` record. Every save is an `artifact-state`
record with `:type 'cart-save`. See Chapter 15.

## Loam

Every projection is a `.slatl` file. Every event kind gets its own
projection. Queries are just streaming reads over projections.

Example projections:

```
~/.lacuna/loam/SYSTEM/cortex-subscription-drift.slatl
~/.lacuna/loam/SAKURA/mood-history.slatl
~/.lacuna/loam/TRAINING/iter-metrics.slatl
```

## Community index

The community index service maintains a signed Merkle-attested slat-
set of all published carts. Each cart is a leaf; the root hash covers
them all. Publishing sends a `publish-cart` message; the index verifies
signatures, updates the tree, publishes a new root.

## The count

As of SLAT 1.0 milestone, 704 `.slat` files across the Lacuna tree
consume the format. That count grows as more subsystems migrate off
JSON and JSONL.

